social_posts.post_text: Currently on view at @untitledartfair booth C28 @longroadprojects, this piece was created with thick layers of charcoal poured on canvas. The work is titled “Fragile” because it is extremely physically and conceptually delicate, a reflection of the currently glaring American political climate surrounding Jews and the longstanding fragile history. Swipe to see Pharrell in the booth ha #contemporaryart #paulweiner #untitledartfair #denverart #charcoaldrawing #charcoal #miamibeach #longroadprojects

Check this bug bleach painting of mine out in the “💭” exhibition at @twfineart on view now in Brisbane next to works by Clay Mahn. The show also includes paintings by Briony Barr, Fran O'neill, Clay Mahn, Saxon Quinn, Michael Weissköppel, Marcus Boelen, and Max Presneill! #contemporaryart #paulweiner #abstractart #abstractpainting #twfineart #bleachpainting #bleach #acidwash

I’m working back and forth between charcoal and computers, reading old texts and finding an outlet for these simultaneously antiquated and contemporary practices on the canvas. Join me on Threads, and let’s discuss what this charcoal piece is. I like this moment of tension for the viewer while looking deep into the unknown, a kind of spontaneity and energy that borders on the macabre. I think that captures something about our zeitgeist. The funny thing about this pic is the paintings on either side look really small by comparison. You know what I’m about to say. I’m shipping a tiny work to New York for @pablosbirthday 21st anniversary group show in October. Mark your calendars if you’re in New York. It’s a gem the size of my hand that you could pluck off the wall when no one is looking, shove it in your pocket, and own it forever. As always, join me on Threads 😃

I’m fascinated by the unknown as a formal painterly value. What does it mean to represent what we don’t know? How can a painting take you to a daydream of a place that doesn’t really exist? We live in a time of such great turbulence, caught between physical reality and a curated digital life of smoke and mirrors. These are the questions we ponder on Threads 👀 🧐 #contemporaryart #abstractart #charcoaldrawing #denverart #abstractpainting #contemporarypainting #paulweiner #studiovisit #zeitgenössischekunst #drawing #abstractexpressionism

That luscious black area at the bottom of the canvas almost makes the top half shine. The viewer is like a cicada crawling out of the ground and coming upon the sunny sky for the first time after 17 years of tunneling in the dirt under the surface. 🐞 PS join me on Threads #contemporaryart #abstractart #abstractpainting #denverart #abstractexpressionism #zeitgenössischekunst #charcoaldrawing #drawing #paulweiner
